      with an imposing retinue of English nobles and Spanish grandees. Philip
      had brought over enough gold and silver to fill ninety-seven chests, each
      a yard and a quarter long. This treasure was piled on twenty carts and
      drawn through the city so that everybody might see it before it was taken
      to the Tower to be coined.
    
    
